         <abstract id="aspace_915b3112b50f58ebb2c70a8d0c297165">The papers include correspondence, memoranda, speech drafts, copies of acts, and printed material relating to Sheridan's Parliamentary career. Materials on the union with Ireland and Catholic emancipation include a letter from John Milner, Bishop of Castabala; memoranda in Sheridan's hand; annotated copies of the proposed Disabilities Act of 1800 and of "The Substance of the Speech of the Marquis Wellesley"; and a survey of heads of Catholic religious communities in England. Sheridan's backing of the Prince Regent is documented in letters to George IV and Lord Holland; speeches and speech drafts; and papers relating to the refurbishing of Carlton House in the late 1780s, including inventories of new furniture.</abstract>
         <origination label="Creator">
            <persname identifier="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n79089813" source="naf">
               <part localtype="agent_person">Sheridan, Richard Brinsley, 1751-1816</part>
            </persname>
         </origination>
    
